post_text: Dear parents of elementary students: The district was informed this evening, September 1st, of a 5th grade student who tested positive for COVID-19. This student was last present on campus 12 days ago on August 20th. It is believed that the student did not come in close contact with other students, while COVID positive, according to exposure tracing and the close contact guidelines set forth by the CDC and TEA. Therefore, the 5th grade class will not have to quarantine and will continue class as scheduled.

post_text: Here is the Elementary Virtual Plan! We need to know by Monday, August 10 if your child will be doing virtual the first 6 weeks! Have a great weekend!!
shared_text:
Mount Enterprise Elementary
August 7 at 10:43 AM ¬∑

Good morning! Below is our Virtual Plan (just for Elementary). I have also emailed this to the emails I have on file. If you know someone not on Facebook, please let them know to contact the school if we do not have an email! Please let us know by Monday, August 10, if your child plans to be virtual. If you told the school you would be doing virtual and you have changed your mind, please let us know! If we do not hear from you, we will assume your child or children will be in person! Have a wonderful weekend!! ALSO-PLEASE SIGN UP FOR MEET THE TEACHER! If you did not receive a SignUp email from your child's teacher, contact the school on Monday and we will get that sent!

Please note: Our situation is continuously changing--everything in the plan is fluid.

post_text:
Attention Parents! If you need a school code for your child, please contact the school Monday-Thursday, 8-5. The link is yourtexasbenefits.com --entering a school code may be optional, so you may not need to call the school for that information.

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

****UPDATE: The Chapter and Greenhand application deadlines have been extended to April 24th!

The following FFA applications are available at the MEISD website at www.meisd.org. Click on the appropriate link at the upper right in the MEISD News section:

Chapter Application is for anyone who has already completed 1 year in the FFA program grades, will be in the 10th or above for the 2020-2021 school year and have a minimum of 1 year of FFA experience
Greenhand Applications are for anyone who will be a Freshman for the 2020-2021 school year and have a minimum of 1 year of FFA experience
Discovery Applications are for anyone who will be in the 8th grade for the 2020-2021 school year and have a minimum of 1 year of FFA experience

Applications are to be emailed back to Ms. Lock no later than April 17th for Chapter and Greenhand and no later than May 1st for Discovery. Interviews will be TBA!

post_text:
Monday, 3/16 8:46 p.m.

Dear MEISD family,

During this week that we are closed, the administration and teachers are diligently working to prepare and plan to educate our students in the likely event MEISD is canceled past this week.

MEISD will give further details and instruction later this week once the decision is made whether to remain closed or resume school.

With all the information coming from the Governor, the Center for Disease Control and the president, I do not foresee a situation that we will open back up next week. Obviously, I could be wrong in my assessment but I wanted to share that information so you can make family plans in the event we do stay closed.

God bless, stay sanitized and keep your social distances. The scary thing about this virus is that many people can be infected without ever knowing it. Those folks could unknowingly spread the virus to people that are more susceptible to health issues. Be careful out there.

Byron Jordan
Superintendent
Mt. Enterprise ISD

post_text:
Friday, 3/13, 6:45 pm

Dear parents, faculty and students,

After receiving a considerable amount of information about this dreaded virus and with schools all around us closing for a week or two, MEISD has made the call to extend spring break a week for most faculty and all students. Students and faculty are currently scheduled to return the following Monday, March 23rd.

Although, as of this writing, we have no confirmed cases of the virus in our county, Shelby County or Nacogdoches County, it is best to approach this unchartered territory with caution over pushing the limits of the unknown.

I, and other schools, are in contact with county health officials, county emergency management and the commissioner of the TEA as information flows in.

We are at a time in our nation that we‚Äôve never seen before. As I said previously, don‚Äôt panic but be diligent and smart in your decision making. I want all of the MEISD family to be safe and avoid this virus. God bless each of you. I will keep you posted as pertinent news comes across my desk.

Sincerely,

Byron Jordan
Superintendent

post_text:
Dear Senior Parents,

This coming Friday evening, November 1st, we will take a few moments before the kickoff of our final home football game to recognize our senior participants in football, cheer, and marching band. The parents, guardians, and immediate family are invited to join these students in the recognition presentation before the game. Please plan to meet at the gate near the south end of the stands near the band at 6:30. A line up order will be posted. We will go over presentation procedures at that time. Please do not come late. The presentation will begin at 6:45. We will not be able to wait for late comers due to UIL rules regarding game start time. If you have any additional questions please contact Mrs. Fryman between 8:00 and 8:40 at 903-822-3721.

Sincerely,

Kim Fryman
Sponsor

post_text: From Coach Jones:
shared_text:
Nick Jones is with Marshall Keith Durrett.
June 7, 2019 at 12:39 PM ¬∑

June 22nd we have a special guest coming to Mt Enterprise... One of the best college pitchers there is Samantha Clakley will be coming to do a softball camp. If you followed college softball this year you know Oklahoma State was one of the best programs in the nation and competed well in the World Series. We are blessed and honored to get to bring someone of this caliber for our kids. Any girls going into 4th-7th grade will be from 9 am - 12 pm/ any girls going into 8th-12th grade will be from 1 pm-4 pm... I encourage any girls who are wanting to be in softball to attend. My goal is to turn this program around and I think we have the talent here to do just that. Again I want to say thank you to Samantha and to all of my parents who have the same vision I do of making Mt Enterprise great again.

Cost of the camp will be 10 dollars per child

If you have any questions please call me 903-722-3460

Thank You
Coach Jones

post_text: Mt. E will be hosting a Basketball Camp on June 17-20 from 9 am - noon. Any incoming 2nd through 9th grader is eligible to attend. The gym will open at 8 am each day of the camp in case anyone needs to drop kids off earlier than 9. If you have any questions, call Coach Durrett at 903.920.2294 or Coach Nick Jones.

post_text:
FFA News! Our kids traveled to Center on Friday to complete a service project at a ranch to earn more hours towards their Lonestar Degrees. This was a great honor for us to be a part of such an event where millions of dollars were exchanged and some of the top breeders and producers were in attendance.

Saturday our show team competed at the Carlisle Show in Henderson TX and brought home more blue ribbons, 2nd place titles and showmanship success! Lake, Gavin, Madeline, Kyleigh, Roberta and Ryan continue to represent our chapter and school with diligence and hard work!

Yesterday, Kristian, Eli, Carlie, Katie and Kennedy represented our chapter at the Longview District Convention. Eli won 2nd place by popularity in the talent team, and Kristian came up a little short of being a district officer, but both represented our chapter and school with pride! For a kid who was terrified of being on stage, he sure stepped up and made us proud!

post_text: This coming Friday evening, November 9th, we will take a few moments before the kickoff of our final home football game to recognize our senior participants in football, cheer, and marching band. The parents, guardians, and immediate family are invited to join these students in the recognition presentation before the game. Please plan to meet at the gate near the south end of the stands near the band at 6:50. A line up order will be posted. We will go over presentation procedures at that time. Please do not come late. The presentation will begin at 7:00. We will not be able to wait for late comers due to UIL rules regarding game start time. If you have any additional questions please contact Mrs. Fryman between 8:00 and 8:40 at 903-822-3721.

shared_text:
Mt. Enterprise High School Band
November 3, 2018 at 11:26 AM ¬∑

The Mt. Enterprise Fine Arts Department will be presenting a program honoring our veterans on Monday, November 12th at 2:30p.m. in the Mt. Enterprise Gymnasium. The program will include performances from the High School Band and Elementary Choir and will feature guest speaker, Mr. Kenneth Miley. We would like to extend a special invitation to our local veterans, and ask that they come be recognized for their brave service. A brief reception for veterans will take place at 2:00pm in the gym lobby. This event is free to the public, and we would love to have our great community there honoring our heroes with us.

Please feel free to contact Jeff Bellgardt with any questions: 903-822-1313.

Thank you, please spread the word!

Congrats to all the kids who participated in the Harvest Festival Show in Longview.

Gavin and Lake W both competed in the Market Barrow Show.

Madeline H- Grand and Reserve Gertrudis and Grand American Division Breeding Heifer
2- 1st place and 1-2nd place

Ryan H had 1-1st and 1-2nd with his Santa Gertrudis Breeding Heifers

Kyleigh L had 1-1st place with her ARB Breeding heifer, 1- 3rd with her Santa Gertrudis Heifer and a 2nd for her American Steer and Reserve Champion American Steer.

Roberta H placed 2nd with her Maine and 3rd with her ORB heifer

Brooklyn F was 2nd in class with her ORB heifer

Kristian D was 3rd place with his Maine heifer

In total we brought home 1 buckle, 3 tumblers, and 14 1st, 2nd and 3rd place ribbons!!!
